---
import Layout from '@/components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — sugaroverflow" description="About Fatima Sarah Khalid">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-serif text-sage-900 tracking-tight">About</h1>

  <section class="mt-8 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <p>
      I'm a developer advocate at GitLab focused on AI and developer experience. I lead programs that combine storytelling with
      hands-on education so developers can see themselves in the future of work. Outside of GitLab, I'm a Research Fellow at Newspeak
      House studying political technology and compute governance.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-12 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-300 bg-neutral-50 p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-sage-900">DevRel at GitLab</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-neutral-900/80">
        I build developer programs that ship quickly but feel intentional: live-coded demos, hands-on workshops, and narrative
        content that shows how humans and AI collaborate. My north star metrics are adoption, retention, and genuine love for the product.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-300 bg-neutral-50 p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-sage-900">Political tech fellowship</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-neutral-900/80">
        At Newspeak House I'm mapping the layers of AI governance—from access to compute, to infrastructure decisions, to the policy
        rooms where those decisions land. The work blends research notes, salons, and playbooks for practitioners.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-sage-900">Philosophy</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-neutral-900/80">
      <p>I believe developers shape policy long before legislation catches up. Every architecture decision is civic infrastructure.</p>
      <p>AI is only useful when it makes humans feel more confident, not less. My work is to translate complex systems into stories that feel actionable.</p>
      <p>Community is a design choice. I choose formats that invite participation instead of applause.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-sage-900">Beyond the work</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-neutral-900/80">
      I'm happiest when I'm facilitating workshops, chasing the best matcha in a new city, or playing board games with friends.
      I grew up split between Lahore and Montreal, and that duality still shows up in how I think about community.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="speaking" class="mt-16">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-sage-900">Speaking</h2>

    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>
        I speak about AI and developer experience, DevRel best practices, and political technology. I'm available for keynotes,
        workshops, and panels.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-serif text-sage-900">Topics I cover</h3>
      <ul class="mt-4 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-2">
        <li class="p-4 bg-sage-100 rounded-lg">AI and Developer Experience</li>
        <li class="p-4 bg-sage-100 rounded-lg">Developer Advocacy Best Practices</li>
        <li class="p-4 bg-sage-100 rounded-lg">Open Source Communities</li>
        <li class="p-4 bg-sage-100 rounded-lg">Political Technology and Governance</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-serif text-sage-900">Speaker requirements</h3>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 p-6 bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg border border-neutral-300">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-medium text-sage-900">Travel</h4>
          <p class="mt-1 text-neutral-900/80">Will travel internationally. Prefer direct flights when possible.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-medium text-sage-900">Accommodation</h4>
          <p class="mt-1 text-neutral-900/80">Hotel room for night before and night of event.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-medium text-sage-900">A/V Requirements</h4>
          <p class="mt-1 text-neutral-900/80">HDMI connection, lapel mic preferred, confidence monitor helpful.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-medium text-sage-900">Accessibility</h4>
          <p class="mt-1 text-neutral-900/80">Please provide accessibility info for venue in advance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <a
        href="/recognition#testimonials"
        class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-lilac-500 text-white rounded-full hover:bg-lilac-600 transition-colors"
      >
        See what people say about my talks →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

